SIMPLE: innovation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Innovation
<hw>In`no*va"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>innovatio</ets>; cf. F. <ets>innovation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>The act of innovating; introduction of something new, in customs,
rites, commercial products, etc.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A change effected by innovating; a change in
customs; something new, and contrary to established customs, manners, or
rites.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The love of things ancient doth argue stayedness, but levity and
lack of experience maketh apt unto <qex>innovations</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Hooker.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A newly formed shoot, or the
annually produced addition to the stems of many mosses.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Innovationist</ent>⟦br⟧
